page.title: 01A SUMMARY OF THE BLOCK 1.
page.content: Our 4x3km block is mostly farmland.We also have some residential areas.Some of{New Waltham}is in the block but mostly the north part.The south part of Cleethorpes and a little piece of Grimsby are in the north part of the block.Most of Humberston is in the south east of the block.There is a disused railway that runs through the south west corner of the block.The railway runs between Grimsby and Louth.There is a preservation society that wants to bring back the railway and they want to put trains back on the tracks. The road that runs from New Waltham to Cleethorpes is the A1098.There are two main roads running through the block the A1098 and the A1031.These roads become especailly busy in the morning and night because people use them to go to work and come home.
